Class ImportBuilder

java.lang.Object
pt.up.fe.els2024.builders.Builder
pt.up.fe.els2024.builders.ImportBuilder
public class ImportBuilder extends Builder
A builder class for importing table data from files and directories. Supports file parsing, folder import with extension filtering, and merging tables. Designed for use with OperationBuilder to perform further table operations.

      public ImportBuilder fromFolders(String foldersPath) throws ParserException, IOException
      Parses a directory structure and maps folder names to tables contained in their files.
      Parameters:
      foldersPath - the path to the root directory containing subfolders and table files.
      Returns:
      the current ImportBuilder instance for method chaining.
      Throws:
      ParserException - if an error occurs while parsing a table file.
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs while accessing the files or directories.
      IllegalArgumentException - if the provided path is not a valid directory.
      IllegalStateException - if the subfolders of the directory cannot be listed.
